sections.name: Please conduct Instant Drug Screen and Alcohol Breath Test assessment BEFORE conducting medical assessment

groups.label: Drugs to be tested to cut-off concentrations as per AS/ NZS 4308
BP Kwinana Refinery will not allow site access for any non-negative illicit or non-declared drugs or > 0.001% BAC

An initial urine drug screen is a screening test only. A result from an initial urine drug screen which is not negative cannot be treated as a positive result unless confirmed by a NATA accredited laboratory with confirmatory testing by GC/ MS.
Level d will not be accepted
TICK THE COMPLETED AND REVIEWED ELEMENTS
Review demographic, medical and occupational history
Physical examination including respiratory and cardiovascular assessments
BAC & Urine drug screen to AS4308
Note: FULL REFINERY ACCESS MUST ONLY BE TICKED IF THE CANDIDATE MEETS ALL REQUIRED CRITERIA
There is no medical restriction to prevent the Candidate undertaking the following activities:

The candidate has one or more abnormality, including undiagnosed or unstable asthma, unexpected glucosuria, (NO INSULIN PUMPS - intrinsically unsafe), major ECG abnormality, major spirometric abnormality or physical/ mental health concerns.
